55.8	Charter_08	Charter 08	Charter 08 is a manifesto initially signed by over 350 Chinese intellectuals and human rights activists. It was published on 10 December 2008, the 60th anniversary of the Universal Declaration of Human Rights, adopting name and style from the anti-Soviet Charter 77 issued by dissidents in Czechoslovakia. Since its release, more than 10,000 people inside and outside of China have signed the charter.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8b/VOA_CHINESE_liuxiaobo.jpg/175px-VOA_CHINESE_liuxiaobo.jpg
